# Styling & UI Guidelines

## Theme Usage

Always use the centralized theme from [src/styles/theme.ts](mdc:src/styles/theme.ts):

- `theme.colors.primary` - Blue (#007AFF)
- `theme.colors.warning` - Orange (#FF9F0A)
- `theme.colors.background` - Black (#000000)
- `theme.colors.surface` - Dark gray (#1C1C1E)

## Component Styling

- Create separate `styles.ts` files for each component
- Use StyleSheet.create() for performance
- Follow the existing pattern in [src/components/](mdc:src/components/)

## Calendar Styling

- Use `theme.calendar` for react-native-calendars configuration
- Blue dots for running (Strava)
- Orange dots for gym (Hevy)
- Multiple dots for combined activities

## Responsive Design

- Use theme spacing values (xs, sm, md, lg, xl, xxl)
- Follow iOS design patterns
- Use proper safe area handling
- Test on different screen sizes

## Loading States

- Always show loading indicators for API calls
- Use consistent loading text and spinners
- Handle error states gracefully

## Component Architecture

- Keep UI components focused on presentation only
- Separate styling logic from business logic
- Use consistent naming for style objects
- Create reusable style utilities when needed
- Follow the single responsibility principle for styling
